author: odeakin
msg: A few changes to fix x-net unit test failures:
- Access the SocketImpl FileDescriptor using reflection so its getFileDescriptor() method can be made protected again, as spec'ed.

- Make SSLServerSocketImpl use SSLParameters to get/set its options instead of going via the SSLSocket. The way this was implemented before meant that multiple accepts on the same server socket were not possible.

- Make the SSLSocketWrapper class function correctly by replacing its SocketImpl with the one in the Socket it is being created with. This fixes behaviour when SSLSocketFactory is used to create a SSLSocket from an existing socket.
